    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-03-19T12:27:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-03-19T12:27:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <head>235. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d235fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 674.84A/3–1757. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                        >Niact</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SJJ1">Sisco</persName> and
                            <persName corresp="#p_HF1">Howe</persName>, approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>, and initialed by <persName
                            corresp="#p_HF1">Howe</persName> for <persName corresp="#p_DAW1"
                            >Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-03-19T12:27:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1957—12:27 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>723. Re: UNEF in Gaza. We are seriously concerned Egyptian return to Gaza
                    assuming character complete rather than token administrative takeover. Cairo
                        2924<note n="2" xml:id="d235fn2">Not printed. (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Ibid.</hi>)</note> contains press reports indicating: (a) local public
                    security functions have been turned over to “Palestinian police” under
                    supervision Egyptian administration; (b) turnover of frontier check-post to
                    Egyptians; (c) headquarters building being handed over Egyptian governor; (d)
                        <gloss target="#t_UNRWA1">UNRWA</gloss> agreed turn over to Egyptians
                    supply, health and education functions former temporarily had assumed.</p>
                <p>However, <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> this morning in phone conversation
                    with Secretary<note n="3" xml:id="d235fn3">See the memorandum of telephone
                        conversation, <ref target="#d234">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> said that reports from <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName>
                    indicated UNEF very much in evidence in Gaza and Egyptians very little in
                    evidence.</p>
                <p>We believe <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> should inform <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRJ1">Bunche</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BMGELM1"
                        >Burns</persName> of our concern over press reports and if proved to be
                    correct to instruct them to take all feasible measures limit present Egyptian
                    takeover to symbolic basis only and refrain from entering into new arrangement
                    with Egyptian officials or finalizing those in process. We assume discussion of
                    these and other problems will of necessity be undertaken by <gloss
                        target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> in Cairo on basis arrangements contemplated by
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.<note n="4" xml:id="d235fn4">In telegram
                        656 from <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, March 19, <persName
                            corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> reported that, when he relayed this
                        request to <persName corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName>, the latter
                        replied that emphatic instructions had been sent to <persName
                            corresp="#p_BMGELM1">Burns</persName> to resist Egyptian pressures
                        pending his consultations in Cairo. <persName corresp="#p_HD1"
                            >Hammarskjöld</persName> also said that the only promise which he had
                        given to the Israelis about UNEF in Sharm al-Sheikh had been not to withdraw
                        without notifying the Advisory Committee. (Department of State, Central
                        Files, 674.84A/3–1957)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
